byline.contributor: Ana Vanessa Herrero reported from Caracas, and Elisabeth Malkin from Mexico City.
byline.original: By ANA VANESSA HERRERO and ELISABETH MALKIN

abstract: Venezuelan National Assembly votes to put Pres Nicolas Maduro on political trial, charging him with with abandoning post and mounting coup against Constitution; move will likely have little effect due to legislature's dwindling power.
lead_paragraph: The dwindling power of the opposition-led National Assembly means the decision to bring political charges will likely have no practical effect.
snippet: The dwindling power of the opposition-led National Assembly means the decision to bring political charges will likely have no practical effect....

headline.main: Venezuelan Lawmakers Vote to Put President Nicolás Maduro on Trial
headline.print_headline: Venezuela Lawmakers Vote to Put President on Trial
